page.title: 01Summary Of The Denmead Area.
page.content: Our area is a combination of rural and urban landscapes. We have studied an area that is mostly agricultural land with a primary village, Denmead. This village is expanding with new housing developments. Our area also includes a suburb, called Wecock, of a large town called Waterlooville. About 65% of our area is farming land. Both arable and livestock farming can be found but the emphasis is on arable farming. Denmead is a large dormitory village that has grown from a small isolated village in the Hampshire countryside. Most of the village is new housing catering for the professional workforce of the nearby towns and cities. Wecock is a new suburb built because of the growth of south-east Hampshire. It has grown since the 1960's.
